However, according to the Federal Migration Authority, the tests will become mandatory for all guest workers in the future.
It is not necessary to take language tests, but also tests into Russian history and the basics of legislation.
Language skills must be proven both for the preservation and extension of the work permit.
Exceptions apply only to citizens of countries where Russian is the official language.
Also excluded from this law are persons who received their training certificates and diplomas before the collapse of the USSR in 1991.
Sense, problem and protection of rights
The entirety of examination offices will be under the aegis of the Pushkin Institute for the Russian Language, the Russian University of Friendship, Moscow State University, St. Petersburg State University and other Russian higher education institutions.
Migrants can take the tests in all cities; more than 160 corresponding centres have already been opened in Russia.
The initiative to introduce the tests was supported by the deputies of the State Duma and the Federal Migration Authority.
