Do not scold, boss!
Nevertheless, many citizens of the Central Asian republics who want to earn their money in Russia admit that they not only cannot master the language of the destination country, but also hardly express themselves in writing in their own language.
Of course, this is not so much their fault, but rather the evil: only a few Turkmen, Uzbeks and Tajiks can afford even a reasonable primary education.
Because in their families there is not even money to feed the children, let alone buying decent clothes, shoes and school things.
As a teenager, these children immediately seize the first opportunity to make money.
"It is difficult without language skills," they admit.
"You feel humiliated and inferior."
Civil rights activists emphasise the following important aspect regarding the law.
The test only needs to hire migrants with legal status.
If you do not have this status, there is no examination and therefore no official work.
Meanwhile, the majority of guest workers continue to be illegally held in Russia.
"Welcome" or "Excourse for unauthorised persons"
Many migrants confirm that it is not easy to maintain official status in Russia.
The reason is bureaucratic hurdles and, of course, the linguistic difficulties.
In addition, the legalization costs money: 12 to 16 thousand rubles.
A fake registration can be made quickly and only for one and a half thousand.
